author: @fisouz
text: Planet size itself is not relevant as the only difference comes down to: Planet.num_docking_spots: The max number of ships that can be docked. As a bigger planet with 5 spots is no better than a slightly smaller planet with 5 spots.  Also, on my code I used a list to control distances and entities associated to each ship: ships_by_distance[0] = distance, ships_by_distance[1] = ship.id, any reason this is a bad choice?  Great vid, btw. I wish I could just sit with you and discuss my halite 2 code :D
